1.Create a Volume from snapshot
-------------------------------------
Create an EBS volume to attach to any EC2 instance in the same availability Zone 

Volume setting: 
\_Volume type
\_Size
\_IOPS
\_Throughput
\_Availability Zones
\_Fast Snapshot restore 
\_Volume Initialization rate : Specify the rate at which  the snapshot blocks are to be 
                                downloaded  from Amazon S3 to the volume 
\_Encryption : Enable if you want to encrypt the volume 

Tags:  Key : Values

Click Create Vollumme 

2.Create a Image from the snapshot
----------------------------------------
Image setting 
\_Image name
\_Descriptoin 
\_Architecture 
\_Root device name
\_Virtualization type       : The virtualization type to be used by the Instance launched form this image
\_Kernel ID   (use default) : The operating ysytem kernel for the AMI
\_RAM disk ID (Use default) : The ram disk for the image 
\_Boot Mode           :
                      \_Use default or  UEFI [ modern OS ] or BIOS  [ older OS ]

\_Block Device mapping : 
                        The Snapshot volume will automatically be selected if you need you can specify the additional volum e
\_Tags

Click create Image

3.Copy Snapshot 
-------------------------------------
Copy a snapshot from one AWS region to another or within the same region 

Source snapshot:  Will be taken automatically 
SnapShot copy details 
\_Description : A description for the snapshot copy 
\_Destination Region: The region in which to create the snapshot copy 

\_Time based Copy [Enabel or Disabel]  : Speicfy a completion duration for the snapshot copy
                                        Operation 
\_Encryption  [Enabel or Disabel ]
\_Tags : 
       \_Key:Value 

Create a copy snapshot 

4.Snapshot settings
--------------------------------
4.1 Modify permission 
---------------------------------
By modifying the permission of the snapshot you can share it with the AWS accoutts that you specify 

Setting : 
\_Sharing Options: 
                 \_Public : Share the snapshots publiccally with all AWS users in this region 
                 \_Private : Share the snapshot with specific accounts 
If you choose the Private then you must add teh instances by using their account ID 
Shared accounts : 

4.2 Snapshot Lock 
----------------------------------
Lock your snapshots to protect them against  accidental or malicious deletion's , to 
store them in WORM (WRITE-once-Read-many)  format ,or to meet your organization's data  
governance  requirement  .While a snapshot is laocked it cna't be deleted

Enable or Disabel Loack snapshot :
Snapshot lock protects snapshots from deletion for a lock duration you specify. Locks can be applied to snapshots in the pending or completed state.

Lock Mode : 
Governance Mode: The snapshot is locked for a specific period ,but it can be unlocked at
                  any time  by users with appropriate permission 


Compilence MOde: The snapshot is locked for a specific period  .it can't be unlocked  
                 after the cooling-off period expire 

Lock Duration : 
               \_Lock the snapshot for
                \_Lock the snapshot until 
Save lock setting 


4.3 Manage fast snapshot restore
----------------------------------
Snapshots that are enabled for fast snapshot restore 
enable you to restore volume that are fully initialized  at creation 

If you click on Enabel for any Az , AWS will : 
1.Pre-warm  the snapshot  
2.Make it instantly fast to restore  in the AZ 

5.Archiving 
---------------------------------
5.1 Restore  snapshots from archive 
----------------------------------------
This brings the snapshot  back to standard storage so you can : 
*Create volume 
*Create AMI
*Copy snapshot
This may take several hours

5.2 Change Restore period
----------------------------------------
This allows you to set how long AWS keeps the restored snapshot in standard storage 


5.3 Archive snapshot 
----------------------------------------
This moves the snapshot to archive tier 
*It becomes MUCH cheaper 
*YOu cannot  use it to create  volumes unitl you restore it 
*Restore time takes up to 24-72 hours 






















